data.description:
VA Loan Assumable 3.125%!!!

3 CAR GARAGE, 3116 square feet, 1.5 story, 4BR 4BA + office + formal dining + bonus/media room. THE CROSSVINE community. Chefs' kitchen with granite, gas cooktop, stainless steel appliances, oversized island, pull-out shelves in all lower cabinets, and walk-in pantry. Upstairs bonus room is prewired for media room. Main floor great room has a wall of custom solid wood built-ins with glass doors and LED lighting above for display and ample storage with hidden electrical access below. Located in the Crossvine master-planned community on a corner cul-de-sac lot that backs to one of several parks. Covenanted for stunning vine covered fences that take 2-3 years to fill in, but this home’s were planted in 2015 and provide privacy NOW in the large fenced backyard with covered patio. Security system & sprinkler system installed. The neighborhood includes a resort-style pool complex, pocket parks and miles of trails and greenbelts. Several outstanding school choices: Randolph elementary, middle, high school. SCUC ISD bus picks up at the corner, walking distance to Founders' Classical Academy (K-HS charter school), and less than 5 minutes from Randolph- accessible via the back gate without any RR Crossings or morning traffic! Quick commute to Lackland, 30min doorstep to gate via I-10. Home is only 8 years old and in excellent condition.

Backyard ~45’x60’

Community Website: https://www.thecrossvine.com/community/amenities

Available Mid-May. Currently occupied. Email, Text or Call to find out more. Getting it on the market early before a PCS. Would prefer to sell by owner to avoid $35k+ agent commission for buyer/seller but as it gets closer to PCS time we may end up needing an agent.

Viewings available by request and appointment only.
data.whatILove: This neighborhood is like an amazing resort- wonderful people, beautiful surroundings, amazing amenities!
